	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>CNROM mapper question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />i have noticed in castlevania 1 and LiteForce (both use cnrom mapper), that the byte of ines file that correspond to prg rom is set to "8" and byte of chr rom is set to "0". 
<br />How can be set to 8 prg-rom if cnrom dont use more than 32k of prg-rom?
<br />and how can be set to 0 if this mapper specifically swap chr-rom?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Disch</b> [ Sat Mar 19, 2005 3:33 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Castlevania 1 and LifeForce are UNROM (mapper 2) which has PRG swapping and CHR-RAM.
<br />
<br />CNROM (mapper 3) has no PRG swapping and CHR ROM.  Solomon's Key is a example of a game which uses this mapper.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


